{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-05322/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-05322"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:53:22"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["medium shot"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["low"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["mobile, tracking"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["group shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A trio of men help carry a woman who has passed out."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05322/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-05322","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05322/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-05322"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05322/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05322/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05322/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05322/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05322/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05322/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05322/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05322/canvas/1/82c40d85-3e61-454e-985d-dbda362e27e5","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-29T20:35:19.910Z","creator":"Tallulah Stallvik","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>While the wedding is meant to be centered on Barbara, her collapse does not seem to interrupt the event at all. We can hear the music and conversations continue in the background; even the people whose table she directly passes do not stop speaking or even look up. At this large event, Barbara has very few people who truly care for her. Perhaps most of the guests are there for similar reasons to Reynolds—because of financial dependency rather than personal connection.</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-05322/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:553.8349358974363,165.61538461538467,891.6266025641028,796.1378205128206"}}}]}]}]}